            <div class="large-12 columns">
            	<p>The University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) expects that all information you present will be true, complete, and accurate/ If you intentionally provide false or misleading information to the Office of the Dean of Students regarding this case, you risk violating the Standards of Conduct of the <a href="http://go.uic.edu/DisciplinaryPolicy" target=\"_blank\">Student Disciplinary Policy</a> and may be subject to disciplinary action.<br />
<br />
The Respondent, the student or Registered Student Organization alleged of violating the Standards of Conduct, will receive a copy of this statement prior to any resolution meeting(s) through the Student Conduct Process. The Hearing Officer or Hearing Panel Committee may have access to this statement as part of a conduct case. You may be contacted to meet with a representative from the Office of the Dean of Students to discuss this statement further or you may be called as a witness at an Administrative Hearing or Hearing.<br />
<br />
If you have any questions or concerns about this Witness Statement, please contact the Office of the Dean of Students at 312-996-4857 or by email at dos@uic.edu. We are located in the Student Services Building Suite 3030.</p>            </div>
